ed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Tindari\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/052\">Antiquarium di Tindari\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">28720\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>A thick marble plaque with extensive blue-grey veining. Intact, edges roughly finished, rear finished only around the edges and projecting unevenly towards the centre. Some surface damage to the face, upper left and lower right.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Lunense\" type=\"stone.marble\" subtype=\"Lunense\" resp=\"#Coccato\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">Very fine-grained, veined, grey, calcitic (with dolomite) marble, likely Lunense. Optical microscopy: heteroblastic fabric with triple points, lineated. Digital microscopy: indistinguishable fabric (identification based on pXRF, digital microscopy, XRD, optical microscopy, stable isotopes analysis)\n\u003CplaceName type=\"provenance\">\n \u003Cref target=\"https://www.geonames.org/6542087/carrara.html\">Carrara\u003C/ref>\n \u003Clocation>\n  \u003Cgeo>44.06294,10.06069\u003C/geo>\n \u003C/location>\n\u003C/placeName>\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">21.8\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">28.9\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">4.0-6.5\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Six lines of latin approximately centred, the last line smaller and set to the left.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.complete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Deep v-cut letters with simple terminal serifs. Some letters tending to curved, particularly V, but also tail to F; L and I almost indistinguishable. Simple dash interpuncts.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Line 1-2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"31\" atMost=\"32\">31-32\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line3\" to=\"line4\">Line 3-4\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"28\" atMost=\"31\">28-31\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line5\" to=\"line5\">Line 5\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"22\" atMost=\"29\">22-29\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line6\" to=\"line6\">Line 6\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"15\" atMost=\"16\">15-16 (F tail to 19)\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462527\">Tyndaris\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u00